                                      "title":  "What are question tags?",
                                      "body":  "A QUESTION TAG is a short question added to the end of a statement. We use them to:\nâ€¢ Check information we think is true\nâ€¢ Invite the other person to agree\nâ€¢ Start or keep a conversation going\n\nThe rule:\nPOSITIVE statement â†’ NEGATIVE tag\n\u0027It\u0027s a beautiful day, isn\u0027t it?\u0027\n\nNEGATIVE statement â†’ POSITIVE tag\n\u0027You\u0027re not from here, are you?\u0027\n\nMore examples:\nâ€¢ \u0027She works in IT, doesn\u0027t she?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027They didn\u0027t come, did they?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027You\u0027ve been to Goa, haven\u0027t you?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027He\u0027s very talented, isn\u0027t he?\u0027",
                                      "grammar_note":  "Tag = auxiliary verb + pronoun\nPositive â†’ negative tag: is â†’ isn\u0027t, do â†’ don\u0027t, have â†’ haven\u0027t\nNegative â†’ positive tag: isn\u0027t â†’ is, don\u0027t â†’ do"
                                  }
                  },
                  {
                      "task_id":  "t1101_02",
                      "type":  "learn_card",
                      "order":  2,
                      "content":  {
                                      "title":  "Question tags â€” tense matching",
                                      "body":  "The tag verb must MATCH the main verb tense:\n\nPresent simple:\nâ€¢ \u0027She works here, doesn\u0027t she?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027They live in Mumbai, don\u0027t they?\u0027\n\nPresent continuous:\nâ€¢ \u0027You\u0027re studying for the exam, aren\u0027t you?\u0027\n\nPast simple:\nâ€¢ \u0027He called you, didn\u0027t he?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027They didn\u0027t come, did they?\u0027\n\nPresent perfect:\nâ€¢ \u0027You\u0027ve met her before, haven\u0027t you?\u0027\n\nModal verbs:\nâ€¢ \u0027She can swim, can\u0027t she?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027You\u0027ll be there, won\u0027t you?\u0027\nâ€¢ \u0027They should know, shouldn\u0027t they?\u0027\n\nSpecial case â€” \u0027I am\u0027:\nâ€¢ \u0027I\u0027m next, aren\u0027t I?\u0027 (NOT \u0027amn\u0027t I\u0027)",
                                      "grammar_note":  "Match the tense of the main clause\nUse the SAME auxiliary in the tag\nI am â†’ aren\u0027t I (special case)"
                                  }
                  },
